}

.exercise2 .main-content {
  /* This is optional, just for clarity */
}

.exercise2 aside {
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: #555;
  border-left: 2px solid #ccc;
  padding-left: 0.5rem;
}
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="meta">
      C:\archive\math\exercises • 3 exercises
    </div>

    <h1>Math Exercises</h1>
    <div class="subtitle">Practice problems with LaTeX rendering</div>

    <nav>
      <a href="/">index</a> /
      <a href="/about">about</a> /
      <span>exercises</span>
    </nav>

    <main>
      <div class="exercise">
        <h2>Exercise 1: Determine the intervals for which Theorem 1 guarantees the existence of a solution in that interval</h2>
        <p>1.a <span set:html={K("y^4 - ln(x)y'' +xy' +2y = cos(3x)")}> </span> </p>
        <p> Since  <span set:html={"ln(x)"}> </span> exists only where <span set:html={"x > 0"}> </span> and all other coefficients are continous for all real numbers the existence of a solution is only guaranteed for <span set:html={"x > 0"}> </span>  </p>
      </div>

      <div class="exercise2">
  <div class="main-content">
    <h2>Exercise 2: Determine whether these given functions are linearly independent</h2>
    <p><span set:html={K("{e^(2x), x^2e^(2x), e^(-x)}")}></span></p>
    <p>We compute the Wronskian:</p>
    <div class="latex" set:html={K(`
W[e^{2x}, x^{2}e^{2x}, e^{-x}] =
\\begin{vmatrix}
e^{2x} & x^{2}e^{2x} & e^{-x} \\\\
2e^{2x} & (2x + 2x^{2})e^{2x} & -e^{-x} \\\\
4e^{2x} & (2 + 8x + 4x^{2})e^{2x} & e^{-x}
\\end{vmatrix}
`)}></div>
    <p><span set:html={K(String.raw`\neq 0`)}></span> so it's independent</p>
  </div>

  <aside class="sidenote">
    <a href = "https://math.libretexts.org/Bookshelves/Analysis/Supplemental_Modules_(Analysis)/Ordinary_Differential_Equations/3%3A_Second_Order_Linear_Differential_Equations/3.6%3A_Linear_Independence_and_the_Wronskian" > Link for proof of Wronskian  </a> but tldr: if two functions are linearly dependent then  <span set:html={K("f(x)c_1 + g(x)c_2 = 0")}>  </span> then diffrentiating this must also be true  <span set:html={K("f(x)c_1 + g(x)c_2 = 0")}> </span> then we can construct this matrix equation 
    <div class="latex" set:html={K(String.raw`
\begin{pmatrix}
f(x) & g(x) \\
f'(x) & g'(x)
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
c_1  \\
c_2
\end{pmatrix} = 0`)}></div> this is only true if <span set:html={K(String.raw`\det \begin{pmatrix} f(x) & g(x) \\f'(x) & g'(x) \end{pmatrix} = 0` )}> </span>




  </aside>
</div>
      <div class="exercise">
        <h2>Exercise 3: Differential Equation</h2>
        <p>Solve the following first-order differential equation:</p>
        <div class="latex" set:html={K(eq3)}></div>
      </div>
    </main>

